- The Prime Power Condition is formalized as `k / P > P`, where `P` is the maximum of the set of prime powers dividing `k`. If there are no prime powers dividing `k` (i.e., `k=1`), then `P=0`, but `k=1` is excluded by `2 ≤ k`.

